@node Controls "Controls"

 Game controls:

 - joystick and/or keyboard

 Sega uses 3-buttons, one for RUN/FIRE, second for using WHIP and third for JUMP.

 Default Amiga keyboard settings:

 - MOVE               = cursor arrows
 - RUN/FIRE           = Z key
 - WHIP               = X key
 - JUMP               = C key
 - BOMB               = X+C key or B key
 - PASSWORD           = SPACE key on continue screen
 - JOY BUTTONS SWITCH = SPACE key in game
 - PAUSE              = P key
 - QUIT               = ESC key

 On original Amiga keyboards does not work combinations of Z,X and C keys,
 but on my external keyboard with Lyra 2 interface it works fine.
 There is possible redefine keyboard in "hota.prefs" file in any text editor or use GUI.
 Just replace RAW key-codes with another ones. 
 (e.g.:Instead of Z,X and C keys to use L.SHIFT($60),L.ALT($64) and L.AMIGA($66) keys.) 
 
 If you use 2-button joystick:

 - Button 1 = RUN/FIRE
 - Button 1 + UP direction = JUMP
 - Button 2 = WHIP

 If you use 1-button joystick:

 - Button 1 = RUN/FIRE/JUMP or WHIP,

 where SPACE key in game toggle between RUN/FIRE/JUMP and WHIP function.

@endnode

@node Settings "Settings"

 Game settings are stored in "hota.prefs" file in game directory ( PROGDIR: ) or S: directory.

 Default settings:

 cddevice="scsi.device"
 cdunit=2 
 music=1
 audiofilter=0
 doublebuffer=1 
 forcenative=0 
 cgx200=0
 gamedatadir="data"
 keya=$31
 keyb=$32
 keyc=$33
 keyup=$45
 keydown=$4c
 keyright=$4e
 keyleft=$4f
 keypause=$19
 keystart=$40
 keybomb=$35

 CDDEVICE 
 - name of the device for cdplayer.library 
   (e.g.: cd.device, atapi.device, scsi.device...)

 CDUNIT 
 - cd unit number (0-7)

 MUSIC 
 - 0=NO music
 - 1=CD music (required CD)
 - 2=HDD music (required converted audio data in "data/audio/" directory)

 AUDIOFILTER
 - 0=audio filter OFF
 - 1=audio filter ON

 DOUBLEBUFFER
 - 0=screen with single buffer
 - 1=screen with double buffer

 FORCENATIVE 
 - 0=if available CGX, then open CGX screen
 - 1=opens a native screen even when available CGX 

 CGX200 
 - 0=nothing
 - 1=attempt for opening CGX screen with height 200 
   (on my wide LCD is with this option nice fullscreen, on other may be stretched)

 GAMEDATADIR 
 - directory, where accessing the game data

 KEYA... 
 - RAW key-codes for the game functions

@endnode

